window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Trish Beckett had her entire life figured out until the night the man she loved left her to die on their kitchen floor.</p> <p>Her only choice is to leave, following her best friend halfway across the country to a small town in the middle of nowhere, Colorado.</p> <p>The longer she's away, the more she sees how much of herself she's buried over the last seven years to become his version of perfection. She vows she will do everything it takes to find herself again. Promising to never look back, not realizing she brought part of her past with her.</p> <p>Layton Kilier is a cowboy that has spent the last year trying to balance working on his best friend's ranch and his mom's battle with cancer.</p> <p>Trish puking on his boots is the last thing he ever thought would change everything, but when she offers to help with his mom, he feels like he can finally breathe again.</p> <p>But just as life finally seems to give them both a break, reality hits. The question is, can they both survive the crash?</p>"; 
